<p>On Linux, I now use Pop!_OS, which is dark by default. I find that <code>ef-deuteranopia-dark</code> looks better with my theme there. Meanwhile, on the Mac, <code>ef-frost</code> works for the light theme and <code>ef-night</code> for the dark theme.</p>
<p>Here&rsquo;s what I do to make this as automatic as possible (F8 is mapped as the key to guggle from light to dark when on the Mac). These are <a href="https://github.com/protesilaos/ef-themes">Prot&rsquo;s EF themes</a>, including the function to switch.</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4"><code class="language-lisp" data-lang="lisp">    (cond 
     ((<span style="color:#a6e22e">eq</span> system-type <span style="color:#e6db74">&#39;gnu/linux</span>)
      (ef-themes-select <span style="color:#e6db74">&#39;ef-deuteranopia-dark</span>)
      )
     ((<span style="color:#a6e22e">eq</span> system-type <span style="color:#e6db74">&#39;darwin</span>)
       (<span style="color:#a6e22e">mapc</span> <span style="color:#a6e22e">#&#39;</span>disable-theme custom-enabled-themes)
       (ef-themes-select <span style="color:#e6db74">&#39;ef-frost</span>)
       (<span style="color:#66d9ef">setq</span> ef-themes-to-toggle <span style="color:#f92672">&#39;</span>(ef-frost ef-night))
       )
     )
</code></pre></div>